Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.27,0:00:36.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.61,0:00:39.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How are Bellows and the others?! \NWhat about the pirates?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.64,0:00:45.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no loss of personnel \Nto the defensive side's vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.49,0:00:48.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy force has been annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.92,0:00:52.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Annihilated... You murdered \Nall of the pirates?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.65,0:00:56.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Affirmative. The enemy \Nforce has been annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.41,0:01:02.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.89,0:01:08.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that about?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.01,0:02:43.01,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,The Villainous Empress
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.39,0:02:46.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The pirate convoy was wiped out?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.85,0:02:51.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Not just their fleet. All of the \Nbastards who boarded my boat, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.58,0:02:55.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With them dead, it's a sure bet the \Nothers will come, hellbent on revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.37,0:02:58.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They really botched this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.97,0:03:03.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Comander! We need to get rid \Nof that boy as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.99,0:03:06.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How about handing him over to the pirates?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.08,0:03:08.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that will cool them off?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.66,0:03:12.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hold up! You're seriously talking \Nabout makin' a deal with pirates?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.32,0:03:13.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what would you have us do?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.83,0:03:16.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I've been sayin', just keep \Nthe Yunboro and as for the kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.40,0:03:18.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What we need to do right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.86,0:03:23.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...is find out what the pirates have \Nin mind, then formulate a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.73,0:03:26.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We can decide on how to \Ndeal with the boy later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.48,0:03:31.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I never imagined something \Nlike this happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.83,0:03:34.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What he said about battling \Nin outer space was true...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.51,0:03:38.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I shouldn't have opened my big mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.86,0:03:43.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been looking for you, Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.90,0:03:46.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a little favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.26,0:03:51.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They really hate me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.85,0:03:55.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Their response defies rational analysis...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.66,0:03:59.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it might lead to negotiating...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.08,0:04:00.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A flying object is overhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.55,0:04:06.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Amy and Bellows! Lower the guns!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.73,0:04:20.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, look...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.46,0:04:23.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I yelled at you before. Are you mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.78,0:04:27.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem. There is no need to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.43,0:04:29.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.74,0:04:34.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Bellows. I've been \Nwanting to speak with you...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.81,0:04:35.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a little present.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.45,0:04:39.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems she wishes you to \Nconsume the animal carcass.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.92,0:04:41.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.61,0:04:44.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo... That's your name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.68,0:04:47.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you slaughter the pirates?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.95,0:04:55.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Does eliminating the enemy require a reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.66,0:04:59.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how things are in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.82,0:05:03.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but here taking a life is \Nsomething that must be justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.23,0:05:09.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is not an issue when you \Nkill a living thing for food?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.33,0:05:15.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, we kill fish and birds to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.34,0:05:19.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But only enough for us to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.91,0:05:22.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't take lives needlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.51,0:05:25.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, the pirates are \Nhuman. We're the same species!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.18,0:05:28.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't take lives lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.90,0:05:33.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If it is forbidden to shed human blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.03,0:05:36.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,why do you possess weapons?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.73,0:05:39.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone feels like it, they \Ncould rob you of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.77,0:05:43.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pirates use that threat to try to \Nget people to do what they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.47,0:05:47.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And so our attitude is that we're not \Njust gonna roll over and die for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.82,0:05:54.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Displaying arms to each other is \Na kind of negotiation in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.60,0:06:03.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We have this expression. "Give fresh \Nwater to the one who catches the fish."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.92,0:06:09.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are those words a recommendation \Nfor humans to aid each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.44,0:06:14.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Because we can't survive \Nunless everybody brings something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.59,0:06:19.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the pirates do not adhere to that rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.85,0:06:23.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we don't agree with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.47,0:06:28.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not letting any pirates have \Nour lives or our possessions!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.32,0:06:34.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But our message is,"There's \Nno profit in attacking us."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.14,0:06:37.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's enough just to communicate that to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.71,0:06:41.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But add death to the mix, \Nthat changes things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.59,0:06:45.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to regain their stance \Nas the threatening side,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.24,0:06:48.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,they're left in the position of \Nhaving to spill even more blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.86,0:06:56.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.54,0:06:57.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.63,0:07:02.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, no matter what people say, we need \Nyour power for run-ins with the pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.05,0:07:06.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a communication device.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.86,0:07:09.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, I'll want you \Nto speak to the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.78,0:07:14.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it didn't end up as it should, you saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.86,0:07:17.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This bird is my thanks for that. See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.93,0:07:24.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.39,0:07:29.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't have a place \Nto go, why not stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.44,0:07:34.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think we'll find a way to \Nmake things turn out smoothly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.26,0:07:37.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She wants me to live on \Nthis boat? Yeah, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.98,0:07:39.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I refuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.26,0:07:41.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Don't refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.82,0:07:42.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I will consider it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.92,0:07:47.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Promise?! You really will consider it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.83,0:07:49.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be getting back...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.53,0:07:55.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo, I'm grateful to you for \Nprotecting Bellows's ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.08,0:07:56.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.90,0:08:04.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.71,0:08:08.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a peculiar phrase...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.88,0:08:23.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.50,0:08:24.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.52,0:08:30.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I never did like them,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.24,0:08:34.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I didn't think they'd \Ndare mess with us like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.40,0:08:38.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, that flying Yunboro worries me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.48,0:08:38.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Marocchi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.88,0:08:43.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Making a fuss over a little incident \Nlike that only makes them cockier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.30,0:08:44.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.31,0:08:48.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what happens to those \Nwho would get cocky with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.84,0:08:54.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what secret weapon they \Nmay have, they're no match for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.83,0:09:03.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Captain, fleet at 3 o'clock... \Nand there's a ton of ships!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.52,0:09:04.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.31,0:09:07.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.59,0:09:11.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Worm, incoming message \Nfrom the cargo ship Atuy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.26,0:09:14.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They've spotted a large pirate \Nfleet in neighboring waters!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.68,0:09:15.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So they're here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.76,0:09:19.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They wish to interlock with our \Nfleet for emergency shelter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.69,0:09:27.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He said the pirate fleet \Nhas at least 30 ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.99,0:09:31.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,30 ships? Almost all of \Nthe pirates in this area?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.96,0:09:35.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, he said they saw a \Nlobster insignia among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.01,0:09:38.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Great Pirate, Lukkage!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.46,0:09:39.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's their course?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.94,0:09:41.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They were spotted here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.55,0:09:45.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At that point, it seems they \Nwere heading east by southeast.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.63,0:09:53.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's safe to say their \Nobjective is our fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.48,0:09:57.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll encounter them by \Nnightfall. Let's change course!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.26,0:10:00.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point. We don't \Nhave the speed to get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.33,0:10:06.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But they've got 30 pirate ships, all \Nloaded to the gills with firepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.05,0:10:10.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even including the small patrol boats, \Nour escort fleet has just 15 ships...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.54,0:10:13.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way they can protect us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.68,0:10:19.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And trying to negotiate with them...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.06,0:10:24.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're coming for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.97,0:10:27.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Only spilled blood will satisfy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.01,0:10:34.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.55,0:10:37.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's ask that kid to help us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.90,0:10:39.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.23,0:10:41.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hear me, Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.84,0:10:45.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.62,0:10:50.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The pirates are heading this way. We'll \Nhave to tangle with them by this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.95,0:10:54.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have already acquired the\N approaching fleet target.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.30,0:10:56.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am prepared to assist you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.25,0:10:59.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what you wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.85,0:11:02.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander, would you talk to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.73,0:11:05.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous! We're in this situation \Nbecause of that brat's--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.36,0:11:09.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless, if we can use that Yunboro, it \Nshould make for a considerable advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.52,0:11:12.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ridget.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.62,0:11:13.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.61,0:11:16.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ridget.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.40,0:11:19.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll speak to you on behalf of \Nthe Fleet Commander. All right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.26,0:11:21.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.14,0:11:26.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me confirm. You say you'll help us,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.19,0:11:30.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but do you recognize that it's your \Nfault we're in these circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.91,0:11:36.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. I apologize \Nfor killing the pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.18,0:11:38.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then one more thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.25,0:11:43.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With your military force, isn't it \Npossible that you could destroy us, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.35,0:11:49.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Affirmative. This machine alone \Ncould wipe out this entire fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.01,0:11:54.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why are you offering \Nto help weaklings like us?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.10,0:11:56.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish to make a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.78,0:11:58.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.11,0:11:59.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bellows told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.92,0:12:03.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You people say, "Give fresh water \Nto the one who catches the fish."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.38,0:12:07.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She also told me that the pirates \Ndon't follow those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.69,0:12:16.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I decided it would be more beneficial \Nto make a deal with you than the pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.13,0:12:23.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to stay here for the time being.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.82,0:12:30.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander, I think we \Nshould accept the boy's deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.29,0:12:31.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.56,0:12:37.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We mustn't neglect to give water \Nto the one who catches the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.82,0:12:54.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmation requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.30,0:12:58.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The mission of this machine is only to \Ndivert the pirates. Is that correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.88,0:13:02.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. All you have to do \Nis get their attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.68,0:13:05.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to restrain yourself \Nfrom attacking excessively.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.27,0:13:09.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand your demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.28,0:13:12.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If at all possible, I will take \Ncare not to cause human casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.40,0:13:12.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}So this is what it's like inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.55,0:13:15.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not enter the cockpit without permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.09,0:13:19.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The hell was that for, \Nyou overgrown tin can?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.25,0:13:29.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unbelievable...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.87,0:13:35.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're entrusting the defense of \Nour fleet to that strange kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.00,0:13:37.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Fleet Commander's decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.30,0:13:39.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand why he made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.16,0:13:41.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.09,0:13:56.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Marocchi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.79,0:13:59.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't we arrived at the Gargantia yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.09,0:14:02.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I sure they'll be noticin' us pretty soon...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.79,0:14:07.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On a night as dark as this, maybe \Neven they have a chance of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.82,0:14:09.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.51,0:14:14.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In this world, nobody exists who\N could beat us in a night battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.01,0:14:16.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.78,0:14:20.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.68,0:14:24.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pirate fleet confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.52,0:14:27.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to begin the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.38,0:14:29.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Up there! Shoot it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.46,0:14:34.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All ships, cannons at the ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.27,0:14:38.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! All ships, commence firing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.02,0:14:47.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me they beat us to \Nthe punch in a night battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.39,0:14:50.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is that Yunboro?! \NIt's flyin' all over the place!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.23,0:14:53.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, already! Counterattack!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.89,0:14:56.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All ships, aim at the enemy fleet and fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.09,0:15:10.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Chezy and Nephilim have been hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.85,0:15:13.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Chezy can't continue fighting!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.27,0:15:16.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Have it retreat. All the \Nother ships, continue...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.76,0:15:20.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Marcus is hit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.48,0:15:22.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep firing! Don't lose this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.45,0:15:25.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even more allied ships have been hit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.81,0:15:30.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Estimate: In 17 minutes, the allied force \Nwill no longer be able to continue fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.39,0:15:34.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we've got no choice. \NWe're going to enter the fray.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.42,0:15:39.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,While avoiding human casualties, disable \Nthe enemy's firepower and mobility.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.48,0:15:41.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.54,0:15:53.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No signs of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.90,0:15:57.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No human casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.56,0:15:58.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.65,0:16:03.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.62,0:16:14.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Crocodile's on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.68,0:16:18.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Grach has reversed course! Are \Nthey tryin' to get away on their own?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.03,0:16:20.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone should be getting \Nhere about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.97,0:16:23.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd better get ready as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.30,0:16:24.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.63,0:16:33.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.74,0:16:34.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Light it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.73,0:16:52.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.07,0:16:52.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pirate attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.65,0:16:55.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Citizens, evacuate to starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.12,0:16:58.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.81,0:17:04.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Move our Yunboros out, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.69,0:17:07.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Send the guards up top!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.66,0:17:13.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Warning: The Gargantia is being \Ninvaded by enemy armored troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.95,0:17:15.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When did they get here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.76,0:17:25.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the only one \Nwith a special Yunboroid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.44,0:17:27.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Empress Lukkage is gonna attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.20,0:17:31.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen Empress Lukkage's \NLobster in a long time!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.58,0:17:34.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Surfing Lobster...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.43,0:17:36.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's heading for the Gargantia!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.39,0:17:39.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All nearby Heavy Yunboros, \Naim for that and fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.39,0:17:46.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's getting through!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.83,0:17:50.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.83,0:18:26.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.18,0:18:28.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like Lukkage just crashed \Ninto the superstructure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.33,0:18:29.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.23,0:18:43.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's climbing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.22,0:18:46.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Send the garrison to superstructure one!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.45,0:18:47.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone evacuate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.53,0:18:50.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the one she wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.61,0:18:52.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.17,0:18:55.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder where Fleet Commander Fairlock is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.76,0:19:03.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm anxious to crush him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.67,0:19:09.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my... You suddenly embrace \Na lady from behind...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.94,0:19:13.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't have anything \Nagainst an aggressive man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.09,0:19:19.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's she trying to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.79,0:19:23.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gung ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.18,0:19:25.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Semper fi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:28.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.55,0:19:48.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems you're good at flying, \Nbut how are you in the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.33,0:19:53.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.83,0:19:56.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe this...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.25,0:19:58.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.51,0:20:01.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Warning to the invading enemy: \NSurrender immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.76,0:20:04.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Surrender?! Lukkage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.25,0:20:06.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not giving me much choice...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.20,0:20:09.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat: Surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.09,0:20:14.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The safety of your lives is guaranteed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.56,0:20:18.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What a bore you are! No matter how \Nmany times you say it, I'll never...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.52,0:20:20.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.62,0:20:25.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Surrender. Surrender. Surrender immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.86,0:20:28.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat: Surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.12,0:20:30.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go... to hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.51,0:20:35.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never surrender... \Neven if it... kills me...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.74,0:20:49.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap! Pull out!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.42,0:20:51.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.32,0:21:06.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That kid did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.45,0:21:09.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.97,0:21:12.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.64,0:21:18.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I keep hearing that word.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.87,0:21:21.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is an idiom denoting gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.50,0:21:24.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gratitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.32,0:21:31.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. He did well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.77,0:21:35.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you intend to deal with the boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.02,0:21:40.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what Chevron would have done...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.67,0:21:43.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My father?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.61,0:21:46.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to let you decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.76,0:21:54.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.66,0:21:56.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll cook you a special dinner tonight, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.87,0:22:05.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,T... Ta... Than...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.11,0:22:09.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
